cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.SN, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on social networks and their implementation on a peer-to-peer architecture. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the decentralization of social graphs onto a peer-to-peer network and the formulation of metrics for both the social graph and projection graph. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the design of socially informed peer-to-peer systems. 
- cs.SN (Social Computing) is another possible category as the paper focuses on social applications and their use of user social graphs. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a less likely category but still possible as the paper discusses the routing of the social graph in the peer-to-peer layer.
